  <md:title>The Triple Axiological Axis: An Introductory Module in Research Ethics</md:title>
  <md:abstract>Research ethics issues in business can be sorted out according to a "triple axiological axis."  This concepts builds on the "double cauce" formulated by Jorge Ferrer in, for example, his book on research ethics, Deber Y Deliberacion: Una Invitacion a la Bioetica.  We have translated this term roughly in English as a double axiological axis and have added a third, social justice.  This module will help students understand issues in research ethics by grouping them under this taxonomy.  It will also encourage them to see research ethics as essential to research activity.  The author would like to acknowledge the support of the National Science Foundation under grant SES 1449489 (Cultivating Responsible Wellbeing in STEM: Social Engagement Through Personal Ethics).</md:abstract>
